			    STPJS 359</div>
  <p class="cont">for there is no redemption for them<span class="footRef">1</span> in this world nor in the world to come.<span class="footRef">2</span></p>
  <p class="std">I could go back and trace every subject of interest concerning the relationship of man to God,
  if I had time. I can enter into the mysteries; I can enter largely into the eternal worlds;<span class="footRef">3</span> for Jesus
  said, &ldquo;In my Father&rsquo;s house are many mansions; if it were not so, I would have told you. I go to
  prepare a place for you&rdquo; (John 14:2).<span class="footRef">4</span> Paul says, &ldquo;There is one glory of the sun, and another glory
  of the moon, and another glory of the stars; for one star differeth from another star in glory. So also
  is the resurrection of the dead&rdquo; (1 Cor. 15:41).<span class="footRef">5</span> What have we to console us in relation to the dead?<span class="footRef">6</span>
  We have reason to have the greatest hope and consolations for our dead of any people on the earth;
  for we have seen them walk worthily<span class="footRef">7</span> in our midst, and seen them sink asleep in the arms of Jesus;<span class="footRef">8</span>
  and those who have died in the faith<span class="footRef">9</span> are now in the celestial kingdom of God.<span class="footRef">10</span> And hence is the
  glory of the sun.<span class="footRef">11</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Righteous Mourners Rejoice</div>
  <p class="std">You mourners have occasion to rejoice, speaking of the death of Elder King Follett; for your
  husband and father is gone to wait until the resurrection of the dead<span class="footRef">12</span>&mdash;until the perfection of the
  remainder; for at the resurrection your friend will rise in perfect felicity<span class="footRef">13</span> and go to celestial glory,<span class="footRef">14</span>
  while many must wait myriads of years before they can receive the like blessings; and your
  expectations and hopes are far above what man can conceive;<span class="footRef">15</span> for why has God revealed it to us?</p>
  <p class="std">I am authorized to say, by the authority of the Holy Ghost,<span class="footRef">16</span> that you have no occasion to fear;
  for he is gone to the home of the just.<span class="footRef">17</span> Don&rsquo;t mourn, don&rsquo;t weep.<span class="footRef">18</span> I know it by the testimony of the
  Holy Ghost<span class="footRef">19</span> that is within me; and you may wait for your friends to come forth to meet you in the
  morn of the celestial world.<span class="footRef">20</span></p>
  <p class="std">Rejoice, O Israel!<span class="footRef">21</span> Your friends who have been murdered for the truth&rsquo;s sake<span class="footRef">22</span> in the
  persecutions<span class="footRef">23</span> shall triumph gloriously<span class="footRef">24</span> in the celestial world, while their murderers shall welter<span class="footRef">25</span>
  for ages in torment, even until they shall have paid the uttermost farthing.<span class="footRef">26</span> I say this for the benefit
  of strangers.</p>
  <p class="std">I have a father, brothers,<span class="footRef">27</span> children, and friends who have gone to a world of spirits.<span class="footRef">28</span> They are
  only absent for a moment. They are in the spirit, and we shall soon meet again. The time</p>
